 class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-5-cathedral-of-evora\">5. Cathedral of Evora<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The medieval city of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/evora\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Evora<\/a> is often forgotten on most traveler&#x2019;s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/portugal-travel-guide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Portugal route<\/a>. However, this historical treasure should be on everyone&#x2019;s list of best places to visit in Portugal! At the heart of the city is the gothic cathedral, which looks more like a castle with its grey stone and turret-style towers. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1.jpg\" alt=\"best places to visit in Portugal\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"best places to visit in Portugal\" class=\"wp-image-58885 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130443\/evora1-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads