#x2019;s highlight is the Moorish castle with its ancient walls that surround the town because these walls are an incredible 1.6km in length! Unusually, visitors are actually allowed to climb up onto the walls and walk their entire length, which is a great opportunity to see the views out over this beautiful part of the Portuguese countryside.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--mustread \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--mustread\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/obidos-portugal\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Obidos: Portugal&#x2019;s most beautiful village<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2.jpg\" alt=\"best places to visit in Portugal\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"best places to visit in Portugal\" class=\"wp-image-58910 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/05\/12130647\/obidos2-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uplo